cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new architecture for recurrent neural networks, which involves optimizing the use of layer normalization and multiple attentions. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the WMT14 and WMT16 benchmarks, which involve processing text and images, respectively. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
